About the Community



Located in the heart of the Silicon Valley, Radius is a quiet Mountain View community offering single family homes and town homes with open floor plans, thoughtful living space, and plenty of room for entertaining.  In this community, you're surrounded by recreational activities and entertainment venues, including nearby Shoreline Park, Downtown Mountain View, and Shoreline Amphitheater.   





Community Features


Mountain View  Features









Overview


Additional Features












Radius models coming soon!











The popular Shoreline Amphitheatre is just minutes from Radius











Upscale Stanford Shopping Center is about 10 minutes from Radius











Rancho San Antonio features 24 miles of hiking trails











The historic Murphy Avenue is about 3 miles from Radius











Nearby Stevens Creek County Park has miles of multi-use trails, shaded picnic areas plus a large reservoir for fishing & boating.











Stanford University a private research school is known for law, engineering, business & medicine located in nearby Palo Alto











Levi's Stadium, the home of the 49er's, is approximately 5 miles away











Nearby Silicon Valley offers opportunity for every lifestyle











Mountain View is conveniently located between the San Francisco and San Jose international airports











Upscale retail can be found at nearby Stanford Shopping Center and Santana Row











Local large venues for entertainment, concerts and sports include the SAP Center and Avaya Stadium











Radius is close to the San Francisco Bay and all of the activities the bay offers











Popular downtown Mountain View is just minutes from Radius











Townhomes at Radius











What Life's Like







Townhomes at Radius





















Popular downtown Mountain View is just minutes from Radius











Radius is located in the highly sought after Mountain View area.  This charming community is surrounded by an abundance of recreational activities and amenities from the popular Shoreline amphitheater to thriving downtown Mountain View.  Homeowners can lead an active lifestyle with over 24 miles of hiking trails at the nearby Rancho San Antonio Park. 
Request Info 







